# Package.json Extension Manifest Rules

## Required Fields
- `name`: lowercase, no spaces (use hyphens)
- `displayName`: Human-readable name
- `description`: Brief description for marketplace
- `version`: Semantic versioning (e.g., "1.0.0")
- `publisher`: Your marketplace publisher ID
- `engines.vscode`: Minimum VS Code version (e.g., "^1.80.0")
- `main`: Entry point (usually "./out/extension.js")

## Activation Events
Prefer specific events over `*`:
- `onCommand:extension.commandName`
- `onLanguage:javascript`
- `workspaceContains:**/package.json`
- `onView:myTreeView`

## Contribution Points
Common contribution types:
- `commands`: Register commands
- `menus`: Add to menus/context menus
- `keybindings`: Keyboard shortcuts
- `configuration`: Extension settings
- `views`: Sidebar views
- `viewsContainers`: Custom view containers

## Example Structure
```json
{
  "contributes": {
    "commands": [
      {
        "command": "extension.myCommand",
        "title": "My Command",
        "category": "My Extension"
      }
    ],
    "configuration": {
      "title": "My Extension",
      "properties": {
        "myExtension.enabled": {
          "type": "boolean",
          "default": true,
          "description": "Enable the extension"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```